    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-27T17:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-27T17:30:00-05:00" n="527"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d527">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">352.115/301: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Valencia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-27T18:00:00-04:30"
                            >August 27, 1937—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 27—4 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>754. Department’s 378, August 21, 3 p.m. I have reached an agreement with the
                    Ministry of Finance (which Señor Negrín assured me this noon meets with his
                    approval) whereby lists of valuables possessed <pb facs="0556" n="544"
                        xml:id="pg_544"/> by Americans may be submitted to the Ministry of State by
                    the Embassy in lieu of the procedure stipulated in the decree.<note n="97"
                        xml:id="d527fn97">By instruction No. 462, September 2, the Department
                        approved his action in obtaining this agreement (352.115/306).</note>
                </p>
                <p>The British are taking no action. The French have protested against the short
                    time limit and will cite their general treaty of friendship in warning against
                    confiscation “which the decree does not contemplate in the case of
                    foreigners”.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
